fields.value: Centro de Investigaciones sobre la Realidad Social (CIRES) [Spain], 1993 (M537V1)

authorName.value: Centro de Estudios sobre la Realidad Social

dsDescriptionValue.value:
The CIRES studies are conducted over a period of months in 1993. In 1993 the studies explore supranational identification, family and time management, attitudes toward immigrants, attitudes and experiences with respect to the public sector, youth, political and economic culture, daily life, crisis in Spain, attitudes and behavior regarding alcohol, tobacco and drugs. Studies are conducted under the supervision of Juan Diez Nicols.

Sample for all months: 1.200 persons of either sex, 18 years old and over, living in Spain. Random sample, stratified by autonomous regions and municipalities according to their size. Field Research: Conducted from January to December, through personal interview at the interviewees' homes, by Redex Network (IOPE-ETMAR). Supervision by A.S.E.P of 20% of the interviews.
